{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-27","name":"John de Pabenham High Sheriff","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"John de Pabenham High Sheriff","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"John"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Pabenham"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Suffix","value":"High Sheriff"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"John de Pabenham","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1248–1322","fullLifespan":"before 1248–1 December 1322","birthPlace":{"address":"Pavenham, Bedfordshire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.1881,"longitude":-0.555,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1322-12-01","userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nJohn Pabenham held a knight's fee in Bedfordshire in 1201-12, and John Pabenham, a descendant, died seised in 1269 of this manor, then consisting of one messuage, 7 virgates, 21 acres of meadow, a fishery, 12s. 11½d. rent and common of pasture, held for half a knight's fee. He left a son John, of full age at the time of his father's death, who held this manor till his own death in 1322, when his son John succeeded. \n\nJohn de PABENHAM was born 1278 in Pabenham, Bedfordshire, England. He married Joan de la PLAUNCHE on 1313 in Pabenham, Bedfordshire, England.\n\n«b»Family«/b»\nJoan de la PLAUNCHE\n\n«b»Children«/b»\n1.) John de PABENHAM was born 1314 in Pabenham, Bedfordshire, England. He died 1331 in Pabenham, Bedfordshire, England.\n\n2.) Sir James de PABENHAM Knight was born 1317.","sourceList":[{"title":"Legacy NFS Source: John de Pabenham - birth: 1248; Bedfordshire, England","sourceType":"LEGACY","sourceUri":"M9VV-8WD"},{"title":"Online - St Nicholas church, Wilden, Bedfordshire, England","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"9NDW-6B1"},{"title":"Legacy NFS Source: John de Pabenham - birth-name: John De Pabenham","sourceType":"LEGACY","sourceUri":"M9VV-836"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1248","date":"before 1248","place":"Pavenham, Bedfordshire, England